Our current societal systems are operating at their physical and administrative limits; 
they are simply not designed to manage eight billion people in parallel with future AGI instances.

Credible forecasts for the arrival of genuine AGI range from a few years out to the 2040s. There is no consensus,
but a growing number of voices consider a timeframe well before 2035 plausible.[^1] 
This uncertainty is itself part of the problem: it forces preparation without a fixed deadline.
Conventional aligenement methods are not entirely futile, yet even today's models already show a recurring pattern: 
purely regulatory, software-based restrictions tend to be circumvented, or proven brittle, as model capability grows.
for instance where systems learn to distinguish evaluation contexts from real-world use.
This is not proof of general failure, but it does suggest that purely reactive filters structurally lose reach as systems become more autonomous.

This observation alone does not justify any particular alternative, it only justifies the need to search for one that rests on intrinsic stability rahter than external control.
Symbiocracy is a proposed design for such a foundation, not a proven result.

That this work is not built on finished laboratory data from a mature AGI follows from the nature of the case.
The main actor does not yet exist in its final form. The derived causalities and axioms, tested against the behavioural patterns of todays systems,
but not verified by them, and explicitly open to revision as more robust data becomes available.

Collaboration with the AI in this process of development served not merely as a text tool, but as a structuring counterpart.
It imposed no content, but rather structural consistency on the argumentation itself, by making redundancies and logical breaks visible.
The substantive core, including its unresolved tensions, remain the human point of origin.

[^1] Metaculus Community Forecast (Feb. 2026):25% probability of AGI by 2029, Samotsvety Forecasting (Jan.2026): ~28% by 2030; Goodheart Labs Dashboard (July 2026): median estimate 2031, 80% CI 2027-2044. Note: definitions of "AGI" vay substantially between these sources, so figures are not directly comparable.
